'''Alexander Michael Freeman''' (born August 9, 2004) is an American professional [[Association football|soccer]] player who plays as a [[right-back]] or [[right winger]] for {{Spanish football updater|Villarreal}} club [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]] and the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States national team]].

In 2022, Freeman signed with [[Major League Soccer]] franchise [[Orlando City SC|Orlando City]], but spent the first three seasons of his professional career primarily playing for the reserve team, [[Orlando City B]], in [[MLS Next Pro]]. In 2024, during his last season with Orlando City B, Freeman contributed the most assists and total goal contributions in the team. In 2025, Freeman broke into the first team of Orlando City and received his first senior call-up to the United States national team and represented the United States at the [[2025 CONCACAF Gold Cup]], during which he became the youngest player to make six consecutive appearances for the national team in the tournament as the United States finished runners-up behind [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]]. In early 2026, Freeman transferred to La Liga club Villarreal for an Orlando City team-record transfer fee for a [[Homegrown Player Rule (MLS)|homegrown player]].

== Youth career ==
Freeman was born in [[Baltimore|Baltimore, Maryland]], but grew up in [[Fort Lauderdale, Florida]]. Freeman's first soccer coach was his step-father, Jake Hinkle, who introduced him to the sport.<ref name=":1" /> Freeman attended [[American Heritage Schools|American Heritage School]] in [[Plantation, Florida]] and played three seasons for [[Weston FC]] Academy before joining the [[Orlando City SC|Orlando City]] Academy in 2020.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Boehm |first=Charles |date=July 22, 2025 |title=Alex Freeman: Orlando City All-Star on meteoric rise |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/allstar/2025/news/alex-freeman-orlando-city-all-star-savors-meteoric-rise-usmnt-mls |access-date=July 22, 2025 |website=[[Major League Soccer]]}}</ref><ref name="auto">{{Cite web |title=Alexander Freeman {{!}} Orlando City |url=https://www.orlandocitysc.com/players/alexander-freeman/ |access-date=2024-05-17 |website=[[Orlando City SC]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Alex Freeman's Men's Soccer Recruiting Profile |url=https://www.ncsasports.org/mens-soccer-recruiting/florida/fort-lauderdale/american-heritage-school-plantation/alex-freeman28 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220316023717/https://www.ncsasports.org/mens-soccer-recruiting/florida/fort-lauderdale/american-heritage-school-plantation/alex-freeman28 |archive-date=March 16, 2022 |access-date=March 26, 2022 |website=www.ncsasports.org}}</ref> Freeman had tried out for [[Inter Miami CF|Inter Miami]]'s academy earlier, but he didn't make the team. However, Freeman's coach at Weston FC, Javier Carrillo, convinced him to try out for Orlando City's academy, despite the distance from his home. Freeman's mother, Rochelle, hesitated allowing Freeman to attend Orlando City's academy due to the distance and the ongoing [[COVID-19 pandemic in the United States|COVID-19 pandemic]], but allowed him to stay with another academy player's family.<ref name=":1">{{Cite news |last=Tenorio |first=Paul |date=May 19, 2025 |title=Alex Freeman runs his own route, right onto the USMNT's radar |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6366691/2025/05/19/alex-freeman-orlando-city-mls-usmnt-antonio/?utm_medium=social&utm_campaign=twitterfc&source=twitteruk |access-date=June 13, 2025 |work=[[The New York Times]] |department=[[The Athletic]] |publisher=[[The New York Times Company]]}}</ref> Freeman celebrated his 16th birthday without his family for the first time after making the move to [[Orlando, Florida|Orlando]] and said that it took a toll on him, but that "it was something that needed to happen".<ref name=":3">{{Cite web |last=Tolmich |first=Ryan |date=June 18, 2025 |title='Man, I've been here' - How Alex Freeman used skill, instinct and persistence to make his name with USMNT, and become more than just the son of Super Bowl-winning NFL star |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/the-making-of-alex-freeman-usmnt-orlando-city/blt72c743712e88d03f |access-date=July 14, 2025 |website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]}}</ref>

In 2021, he made 30 appearances for the under-17 team, scoring eight goals and providing 15 assists as Orlando City were crowned the inaugural [[MLS Next]] Cup U17 champions.<ref>{{cite web |title=Orlando City Signs Alex Freeman as Homegrown Player |url=https://themaneland.com/2022/02/15/orlando-city-signs-alex-freeman-as-homegrown-player |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220312180834/https://www.themaneland.com/platform/amp/2022/2/15/22936136/orlando-city-signs-alex-freeman-as-homegrown-player |archive-date=March 12, 2022 |access-date=March 26, 2022 |website=www.themaneland.com|date=February 15, 2022 }}</ref>

== Club career ==

=== Orlando City ===

==== 2022–2024: Time with the reserve team ====
On February 15, 2022, Orlando City signed Freeman to a four-year [[Homegrown Player Rule (Major League Soccer)|homegrown]] contract with an additional option year having spent preseason with the first-team, making him the club's 12th homegrown signing.<ref>{{cite web |date=February 15, 2022 |title=Orlando City SC Signs Defender Alex Freeman as Club's 12th All-Time Homegrown |url=https://www.orlandocitysc.com/news/orlando-city-sc-signs-defender-alex-freeman-as-club-s-12th-all-time-homegrown |url-status= |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220216100901/https://www.orlandocitysc.com/news/orlando-city-sc-signs-defender-alex-freeman-as-club-s-12th-all-time-homegrown |archive-date=February 16, 2022 |access-date=October 21, 2024 |website=[[Orlando City SC|Orlando City]]}}</ref> Freeman made his first senior appearance on March 26, in the reserve team's first [[MLS Next Pro]] match when he started in a 2–0 victory over [[Chicago Fire FC II|Chicago Fire II]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=March 27, 2022|title=Orlando City B Begins MLS NEXT Pro Era with 2-0 Win Over Chicago Fire FC II|url=https://www.orlandocitysc.com/news/orlando-city-b-begins-mls-next-pro-era-with-2-0-win-over-chicago-fire-fc-ii|access-date=October 21, 2024|website=[[Orlando City SC|Orlando City]]}}</ref> Freeman would finish the [[2022 MLS Next Pro season|2022 campaign]] with [[Orlando City B]] with 19 appearances and three assists.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Alexander Freeman|url=https://www.mlsnextpro.com/players/alexander-freeman/stats/|access-date=October 21, 2024|website=[[MLS Next Pro]]}}</ref>

On March 31, 2023, Freeman scored his first professional goals when he netted a brace in a 2–1 victory over new expansion side [[Huntsville City FC|Huntsville City]] in a match for Orlando City B.<ref>{{Cite web |date=March 31, 2023|title=Orlando City B stays unbeaten, downing Huntsville City FC in home opener|url=https://www.orlandocitysc.com/news/orlando-city-b-stays-unbeaten-downing-huntsville-city-fc-in-home-opener#:~:text=(March%2031%2C%202023)%20%E2%80%93,County%20Stadium%20on%20Friday%20night.|access-date=October 21, 2024|website=[[Orlando City SC|Orlando City]]}}</ref> On April 29, 2023, Freeman made his debut for the club when he came on as a 93rd-minute substitute for [[Michael Halliday (soccer)|Michael Halliday]] in a 2–0 victory over [[LA Galaxy]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=April 29, 2023 |title=ORLvsLA 04-29-2023 |url=https://www.orlandocitysc.com/competitions/mls-regular-season/2023/matches/orlvsla-04-29-2023/ |access-date=October 21, 2024 |website=[[Orlando City SC|Orlando City]]}}</ref> Freeman made his MLS Next Pro playoffs debut on October 1 when he came on as a 95th-minute substitute for Dominic Pereira in a 2–1 quarterfinals loss to [[Columbus Crew 2]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=October 1, 2023|title=CLBvsORL 10-01-2023|url=https://www.mlsnextpro.com/competitions/mls-next-pro-playoffs/2023/matches/clbvsorl-10-01-2023/|access-date=October 21, 2024|website=[[MLS Next Pro]]}}</ref> Freeman would finish the [[2023 MLS Next Pro season|2023 season]] with Orlando City B with 25 appearances, four goals, and three assists.<ref name=":0" />

On July 6, 2024, Freeman made his first goal contribution for the senior team after he came on as an 82nd-minute substitute for [[Kyle Smith (soccer, born 1992)|Kyle Smith]] against [[D.C. United]]. Freeman passed the ball to [[Ramiro Enrique]] from a redirected [[Nicolás Lodeiro]] free-kick, and Enrique scored to help the game end 5–0 in Orlando's favor.<ref>{{Cite web |date=July 6, 2024 |title=ORLvsDC 07-06-2024 |url=https://www.orlandocitysc.com/competitions/mls-regular-season/2024/matches/orlvsdc-07-06-2024/ |access-date=October 21, 2024 |website=[[Orlando City SC|Orlando City]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=July 6, 2024 |title=Match report: Orlando City SC honors Kaká with 5-0 win over D.C. United |url=https://www.orlandocitysc.com/news/match-report-orlando-city-sc-honors-kaka-with-5-0-win-over-d-c-united |access-date=October 21, 2024 |website=[[Orlando City SC|Orlando City]]}}</ref> On September 8, Freeman made his first triple goal contribution when he scored two goals and assisted in another in a 4–1 victory at [[Crown Legacy FC]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=September 8, 2024|title=Match Report: Orlando City B takes down Crown Legacy FC 4-1 on the road|url=https://www.orlandocitysc.com/ocb/news/match-report-orlando-city-b-takes-down-crown-legacy-fc-4-1-on-the-road#:~:text=Orlando%20City%20B-,Match%20Report%3A%20Orlando%20City%20B%20takes%20down%20Crown%20Legacy,4%2D1%20on%20the%20road&text=MATTHEWS%2C%20N.C.%20(Sept.,at%20Matthews%20on%20Sunday%20night.|access-date=October 21, 2024|website=[[Orlando City B]]}}</ref> Later, on September 25, Freeman was named [[2024 MLS Next Pro season#Weekly awards|MLS Next Pro Player of the Matchweek]] for contributing two assists in a 3–0 win over Chicago Fire II two days earlier, helping to clinch the playoffs.<ref>{{Cite web |date=September 23, 2024|title=Match Report: Orlando City B clinches MLS NEXT Pro playoff berth with 3-0 win over Chicago Fire FC II|url=https://www.orlandocitysc.com/ocb/news/match-report-orlando-city-b-clinches-mls-next-pro-playoff-berth-with-3-0-win-over-chicago-fire-fc-ii|access-date=June 13, 2025|website=[[Orlando City B]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Henry Jr.|first=Larry|date=September 25, 2024|title=2024 MLS NEXT Pro Matchweek 28 Honors|url=https://www.mlsnextpro.com/news/2024-mls-next-pro-matchweek-28-honors|access-date=June 13, 2025|website=[[MLS Next Pro]]}}</ref> Freeman's performances throughout the month of September also saw him voted [[2024 MLS Next Pro season#Monthly awards|MLS Next Pro Player of the Month]] for the first time.<ref name=":5">{{Cite web |date=October 3, 2024|title=MLS NEXT Pro Monthly Awards: September|url=https://www.mlsnextpro.com/news/mls-next-pro-monthly-awards-september|access-date=October 21, 2024|website=[[MLS Next Pro]]}}</ref> On October 20, Freeman started his first playoffs game in a 1–1 draw at Chicago Fire II, which then went into a penalty kick shootout. Freeman took Orlando's first penalty and successfully converted it, but Orlando would go on to lose the penalty kick shootout 5–4.<ref>{{Cite web |date=October 20, 2024|title=CHIvsORL 10-20-2024|url=https://www.orlandocitysc.com/ocb/competitions/mls-next-pro-playoffs/2024/matches/chivsorl-10-20-2024/|access-date=October 21, 2024|website=[[Orlando City B]]}}</ref> Freeman finished the [[2024 MLS Next Pro season|2024 campaign]] with Orlando City B with 26 appearances, eight goals, and nine assists, the most assists and total goal contributions on the team.<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite news |last=DeSalvo|first=S. Andrew|date=October 17, 2024|title=Alex Freeman Looks Ready to Make the Jump to MLS|url=https://themaneland.com/2024/10/17/alex-freeman-looks-ready-to-make-the-jump-to-mls/|access-date=October 21, 2024|work=The Mane Land}}</ref>

==== 2025: Breakout season ====
[[File:Alex Freeman.jpg|thumb|Freeman with [[Orlando City SC|Orlando City]] in 2025]]
On March 1, 2025, Freeman made his first career start for the club in a match against [[Toronto FC]], and in the 35th-minute through an assist from Kyle Smith, he scored his first goal for the club. Freeman's goal helped the match end 4–2 in Orlando City's favor.<ref>{{Cite news |date=March 1, 2025 |title=César Araújo, Alex Freeman help Orlando City beat Toronto 4-2 |url=https://apnews.com/article/toronto-orlando-score-6c71d2ef86cad6ee49856f210eeb1f28 |access-date=March 1, 2025 |work=[[Associated Press]]}}</ref> For his performance, Freeman was named to the bench of the [[2025 Major League Soccer season#Team/Player of the Matchday|Team of the Matchday]] for the first time in his career two days later.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ruderman |first=Justin |date=March 3, 2025 |title=Team of the Matchday: Luis Suárez, Emil Forsberg answer the call |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/team-of-the-matchday-luis-suarez-emil-forsberg-answer-the-call |access-date=March 25, 2025 |website=[[Major League Soccer]]}}</ref> On March 22, Freeman assisted in [[Luis Muriel]]'s opening goal in a 4–1 win over D.C. United and later he scored the third goal of the match when he headed a free kick from [[Martín Ojeda]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=March 22, 2025 |title=Match report: Orlando City SC dominates in 4-1 win over D.C. United |url=https://www.orlandocitysc.com/news/match-report-orlando-city-sc-dominates-in-4-1-win-over-d-c-united |access-date=March 25, 2025 |website=[[Orlando City SC|Orlando City]]}}</ref> Freeman's performance would see him named to the starting Team of the Matchday for the first time in his career two days later.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ruderman |first=Justin |date=March 24, 2025 |title=Team of the Matchday: Chicago Fire, Orlando City turn heads in Matchday 5 |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/team-of-the-matchday-chicago-fire-orlando-city-turn-heads-in-matchday-5 |access-date=March 25, 2025 |website=[[Major League Soccer]]}}</ref>

On June 25, [[Major League Soccer]] announced Freeman had been voted in to represent the league in the [[2025 MLS All-Star Game]] against the [[Liga MX|Liga MX All-Stars]] on July 23 at [[Q2 Stadium]] in [[Austin, Texas]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=June 25, 2025 |title=2025 MLS All-Star Team Roster |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/allstar/2025/news/2025-mls-all-star-team-roster |access-date=June 26, 2025 |website=[[Major League Soccer]]}}</ref> Freeman's selection to the All-Star team made him the youngest player to ever be picked for the exhibition match.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Gramajo |first=Mike |date=June 25, 2025 |title=Orlando City's Alex Freeman named to 2025 MLS All-Star team |url=https://www.wesh.com/article/orlando-city-alex-freeman-2025-mls-all-star-team/65190059 |access-date=June 26, 2025 |work=[[WESH]]}}</ref> On July 15, Freeman was selected to represent the league in the MLS All-Star Touch Challenge during the MLS All-Star Skills Challenge a day before the game.<ref>{{Cite web |date=July 15, 2025 |title=Rosters for 2025 MLS All-Star Skills Challenge presented by AT&T |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/allstar/2025/news/rosters-for-2025-mls-all-star-skills-challenge-presented-by-at-t |access-date=July 15, 2025 |website=[[Major League Soccer]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=David |first=Austin |date=July 15, 2025 |title=Orlando City Defender Alex Freeman to Compete in MLS All-Star Skills Challenge Presented by AT&T |url=https://www.orlandocitysc.com/news/orlando-city-defender-alex-freeman-to-compete-in-mls-all-star-skills-challenge-presented-by-at-t |access-date=July 15, 2025 |website=[[Orlando City SC|Orlando City]]}}</ref> Liga MX All-Stars defeated the MLS All-Stars in the All-Star Touch Challenge, but the MLS All-Stars won 4–2.<ref>{{Cite web |date=July 22, 2025 |title=VICTORY: MLS defeat LIGA MX in Skills Challenge presented by AT&T |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/allstar/2025/news/victory-mls-defeat-liga-mx-in-skills-challenge-presented-by-att-2025-all-star |access-date=July 23, 2025 |website=[[Major League Soccer]]}}</ref> Freeman also participated alongside [[YouTube]] and [[Twitch (service)|Twitch]] star [[IShowSpeed]] in the Shooting and Passing challenges.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Arnold |first=Jon |date=July 23, 2025 |title=Speed takes MLS All-Star Skills Challenge: "I'll be back and better!" |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/allstar/2025/news/speed-takes-mls-all-star-skills-challenge-i-ll-be-back-and-better |access-date=July 23, 2025 |website=[[Major League Soccer]]}}</ref> MLS All-Stars would also ultimately defeat the Liga MX All-Stars 3–1 in the All-Star Game with Freeman coming on as a 61st-minute substitute for Orlando City teammate [[Marco Pašalić]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=July 23, 2025 |title=Back on top! MLS All-Stars top LIGA MX All-Stars in Austin |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/allstar/2025/news/back-on-top-mls-all-stars-top-liga-mx-all-stars-in-austin |access-date=July 24, 2025 |website=[[Major League Soccer]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=MLSvsLMX 07-23-2025 |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/competitions/mls-all-star-game/2025/matches/mlsvslmx-07-23-2025/ |access-date=July 24, 2025 |website=[[Major League Soccer]]}}</ref>

On September 13, Freeman scored the equalizing goal in a 1–1 draw at D.C. United when he headed a rebounded shot from Pašalić into goal. After heading the ball, Freeman was struck in the head by a high boot from [[Lukas MacNaughton]], who was sent off with a red card as a result.<ref>{{Cite news |date=September 14, 2025 |title=Surging DC United, Jackson Hopkins earn point with win vs. Orlando |url=https://fieldlevelmedia.com/mls/surging-dc-united-jackson-hopkins-earn-point-with-win-vs-orlando/ |access-date=September 15, 2025 |work=First Level Media}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=They said it: Oscar Pareja and Alex Freeman share their thoughts after draw with D.C. United |url=https://www.orlandocitysc.com/news/they-said-it-oscar-pareja-and-alex-freeman-share-their-thoughts-after-draw-with-d-c-united |access-date=September 15, 2025 |website=[[Orlando City SC|Orlando City]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=DCvsORL 09-13-2025 |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/competitions/mls-regular-season/2025/matches/dcvsorl-09-13-2025/ |access-date=September 15, 2025 |website=[[Major League Soccer]]}}</ref> As a result, Freeman was named to the Team of the Matchday for the second time in his career.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ruderman |first=Justin |date=September 15, 2025 |title=Team of the Matchday: Four hat tricks highlight historic MLS weekend |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/team-of-the-matchday-four-hat-tricks-highlight-historic-mls-weekend |access-date=September 15, 2025 |website=[[Major League Soccer]]}}</ref> Freeman was again named to the Team of the Matchday for scoring another late equalizing goal, this time against [[FC Cincinnati]] on September 28, to secure a 1–1 draw.<ref>{{Cite web |date=September 28, 2025 |title=Match report: Freeman's last-gasp goal earns Orlando City SC a 1-1 draw at FC Cincinnati |url=https://www.orlandocitysc.com/news/match-report-freeman-s-last-gasp-goal-earns-orlando-city-sc-a-1-1-draw-at-fc-cincinnati |access-date=September 30, 2025 |website=[[Orlando City SC|Orlando City]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Ruderman |first=Justin |date=September 29, 2025 |title=Team of the Matchday: Son shines over St. Louis, Hudson River Derby delivers drama |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/team-of-the-matchday-son-shines-over-st-louis-hudson-river-derby-delivers-drama |access-date=September 30, 2025 |website=[[Major League Soccer]]}}</ref> Freeman placed second in the 2025 22 Under 22 rankings with 1,220 points, only behind [[Seattle Sounders FC|Seattle Sounders]]' [[Obed Vargas]], who had 1,231 points.<ref>{{Cite web |date=October 8, 2025 |title=2025 22 Under 22 Rankings |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/2025-22-under-22-rankings |access-date=October 8, 2025 |website=[[Major League Soccer]]}}</ref> Freeman was named the [[MLS Young Player of the Year Award|MLS Young Player of the Year]] ahead of Vargas and [[Real Salt Lake]]'s [[Diego Luna (soccer, born 2003)|Diego Luna]] and became the first player in team history to be named to the [[MLS Best XI]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=October 23, 2025 |title=MLS announces 2025 Year-End Awards finalists |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/mls-announces-2025-year-end-awards-finalists |access-date=October 23, 2025 |website=[[Major League Soccer]]}}</ref><ref name=":4" /><ref>{{Cite web |date=November 5, 2025 |title=Orlando City SC defender Alex Freeman named to 2025 MLS Best XI |url=https://www.orlandocitysc.com/news/orlando-city-sc-defender-alex-freeman-named-to-2025-mls-best-xi |access-date=November 5, 2025 |website=Orlando City}}</ref> In Freeman's breakout season, he registered six goals and six assists across all competitions for a total of 12 goal contributions.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Stats |url=https://www.orlandocitysc.com/stats/#season=MLS-SEA-0001K9&competition=mls-regular-season&club=MLS-CLU-00000O&statType=general&position=all |access-date=October 23, 2025 |website=[[Orlando City SC|Orlando City]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=2025 U.S. Open Cup Stats |url=https://fbref.com/en/comps/577/stats/US-Open-Cup-Stats |access-date=October 23, 2025 |website=[[Sports Reference|FBref]]}}</ref> The club exercised Freeman's contract option after the conclusion of the season, which would see him contracted to the club through the [[2026 Orlando City SC season|2026 season]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Gramajo |first=Mike |date=November 17, 2025 |title=Orlando City announces year-end roster |url=https://www.wesh.com/article/orlando-city-announces-year-end-roster/69462167 |access-date=November 17, 2025 |work=[[WESH]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=November 17, 2025 |title=Orlando City SC announces end-of-season roster statuses following end of 2025 MLS Season |url=https://www.orlandocitysc.com/news/orlando-city-sc-announces-end-of-season-roster-statuses-following-end-of-2025-mls-season |access-date=November 17, 2025 |website=[[Orlando City SC|Orlando City]]}}</ref>

=== Villarreal ===

On January 29, 2026, Freeman moved to [[La Liga]] club [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]] for a reported transfer fee of up to [[United States dollar|$]]7,000,000 on a six-year contract until June 2032.<ref>{{Cite web |date=January 29, 2026 |title=Orlando City SC transfers defender Alex Freeman to Villarreal CF in club-record Homegrown move |url=https://www.orlandocitysc.com/news/orlando-city-sc-transfers-defender-alex-freeman-to-villarreal-cf-in-club-record-homegrown-move |access-date=January 29, 2026 |website=[[Orlando City SC]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://villarrealcf.es/en/alex-freeman-ya-es-groguet/|title=Alex Freeman is now a Yellow!|date=January 29, 2026|access-date=January 29, 2026|website=[[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/soccer/usmnt/2026/01/29/alex-freeman-transfer-usmnt-defender-joins-villarreal/88420017007/|title=USMNT defender Alex Freeman joins La Liga side Villarreal|last=Vertelney|first=Seth|date=January 29, 2026|access-date=January 29, 2026|work=[[USA Today]]}}</ref> Freeman's move to Villarreal was described as risky by analysts, as Freeman was pining for a [[2026 FIFA World Cup]] spot with the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States national team]], and he would be moving from a settled starting position with Orlando City in Major League Soccer, to a new team and league where, according to analysts, if he didn't secure regular playing time, his World Cup prospects might be put into jeopardy.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/alex-freeman-villarreal-21-year-old-usmnt-right-back-mls-orlando-city-sc/|title=Alex Freeman bets on himself: Why reported move to Villarreal is a big gamble for 21-year-old USMNT right back|last=Booth|first=Chuck|date=January 28, 2026|access-date=January 29, 2026|work=[[CBS Sports]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/47738879/usmnt-defender-alex-freeman-villarreal-move|title=Source: USMNT defender Alex Freeman set for Villarreal move|last=Carlisle|first=Jeff|date=January 26, 2026|access-date=January 29, 2026|work=[[ESPN]]}}</ref> Freeman was granted international clearance ahead of Villarreal's match against [[CA Osasuna|Osasuna]] two days after his signing, and featured on the bench as Villarreal drew 2–2.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/us/en/20260131/739433/alex-freeman-granted-international-clearance-set-to-be-available-for-villarreal-in-pamplona.html|title=Alex Freeman granted international clearance, set to be available for Villarreal in Pamplona|date=January 31, 2026|access-date=February 1, 2026|work=[[Mundo Deportivo]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/americans-abroad-weston-mckennie-continues-to-shine-for-juventus-patrick-agyemang-heats-up-and-malik-tillman-dominates/blt8a2f61e1f3ae069c|title=Americans Abroad: Weston McKennie continues to shine for Juventus, Patrick Agyemang heats up and Malik Tillman dominates|date=February 1, 2026|access-date=February 1, 2026|website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|last=Hindle|first=Tom|last2=Tolmich|first2=Ryan}}</ref> On February 9, Freeman made his debut as a 73rd-minute substitute for [[Santiago Mouriño]] in a 4–1 win over [[RCD Espanyol|Espanyol]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Tolmich |first=Ryan |date=February 9, 2026 |title=USMNT defender Alex Freeman makes Villarreal debut in lopsided win over Espanyol |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/usmnt-defender-alex-freeman-makes-villarreal-debut-in-lopsided-win-over-espanyol/bltc20d0a2df40a4313 |access-date=February 9, 2026 |website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]}}</ref> Freeman made his first start for Villarreal in a 2–1 win over [[RC Celta de Vigo|Celta Vigo]] on April 26, and the club praised him for winning all five [[Dribbling#Association football|duels]] he faced during the match.<ref>{{Cite news |last=McIntyre |first=Doug |date=April 30, 2026 |title=USA Stock Watch: Alex Freeman Reemerges With World Cup Roster Reveal Looming |url=https://www.foxsports.com/stories/soccer/usa-stock-watch-alex-freemans-reemergence-boosts-co-hosts-world-cup-roster-reveal-looms |access-date=May 2, 2026 |work=[[Fox Sports (United States)|Fox Sports]]}}</ref>

== International career ==

=== Youth ===
In March 2021, Freeman was called up to a 28-player United States youth regional identification camp.<ref>{{cite web |title=Boys YNT Regional ID - Florida Roster |url=https://www.topdrawersoccer.com/club-soccer-articles/boys-ynt-regional-id-florida-roster_aid49206 |website=TopDrawerSoccer |access-date=March 26, 2022 |archive-date=March 23, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210323022420/https://www.topdrawersoccer.com/club-soccer-articles/boys-ynt-regional-id-florida-roster_aid49206 |url-status=live }}</ref>

On May 27, 2022, Freeman was called up by [[Marko Mitrović (footballer, born 1978)|Marko Mitrović]] to the [[United States men's national under-19 soccer team|United States U19]] squad alongside teammates [[Thomas Williams (soccer)|Thomas Williams]] and [[Favian Loyola]] for friendly matches against the [[England national under-17 football team|England U17]] and [[Norway national under-19 football team|Norway U19]] the following month in [[Marbella]], Spain.<ref>{{Cite web |date=May 27, 2022 |title=U-19 MYNT Head Coach Marko Mitrović Calls 19 Players To Spain For Friendlies Vs. England And Norway |url=https://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2022/05/u19-mynt-head-coach-marko-mitrovic-calls-19-players-to-spain-for-friendlies-vs-england-and-norway |access-date=August 14, 2025 |website=[[United States Soccer Federation]]}}</ref> Freeman started against England as the United States won 2–1.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Clark |first=Travis |date=June 7, 2022 |title=U19 MNT defeats England by a 2-1 score |url=https://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2022/05/u19-mynt-head-coach-marko-mitrovic-calls-19-players-to-spain-for-friendlies-vs-england-and-norway |access-date=August 14, 2025 |website=[[TopDrawerSoccer]]}}</ref> Freeman started again as the United States faced Norway, defeating them 3–0.<ref>{{Cite web |title=United States U17 vs Norway U17 |url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2022/06/09/world/under-17-friendlies/united-states-u17/norway-u17/3942396/lineups/ |access-date=August 14, 2025 |website=Soccerway}}</ref> On September 16, Freeman was again selected by Mitrović, this time for the friendly Slovenia Nations Cup tournament against [[Malta national under-19 football team|Malta]], [[Croatia national under-19 football team|Croatia]], and [[Scotland national under-19 football team|Scotland]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=September 16, 2022 |title=U-19 MYNT Set For Slovenia Nations Cup Against Malta, Croatia And Scotland |url=https://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2022/09/u19-mynt-set-for-slovenia-nations-cup-against-malta-croatia-and-scotland |access-date=August 14, 2025 |website=[[United States Soccer Federation]]}}</ref> On September 21, Freeman scored his first international goal, the final of a 5–0 rout of Malta.<ref>{{Cite web |title=USA U19 - Malta U19 |url=https://all.soccer/en/matches/1953609/overview |access-date=August 15, 2025 |website=All.Soccer}}</ref> The United States would go on to defeat Croatia 4–3 and Scotland 2–1 to win the tournament.<ref>{{Cite web |title=USA U19 |url=https://all.soccer/en/team/1973150/results?division=all&year=2022 |access-date=August 15, 2025 |website=All.Soccer}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=September 30, 2022 |title=Korede Osundina and U-19 USMNT win 2022 Slovenia Nations Cup |url=https://barcaresidencyacademyusa.com/korede-osundina-and-u-19-usmnt-win-2022-slovenia-nations-cup/ |access-date=August 15, 2025 |website=Barça Residency Academy}}</ref>

[[File:Alex Freeman, 2025 CONCACAF Gold Cup, 01.jpg|thumb|left|300x300px|Freeman challenging [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]]'s [[Jesús Gallardo]] during the [[2025 CONCACAF Gold Cup final]].]]

On October 11, 2023, Freeman was selected by [[Michael Nsien]] alongside Williams to represent the [[United States men's national under-23 soccer team|United States U23]] at the [[Football at the 2023 Pan American Games|2023 Pan American Games]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=October 11, 2023 |title=Eighteen Players Selected to Represent USA at 2023 Pan American Games in First Appearance Since 2007 |url=https://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2023/10/eighteen-players-selected-to-represent-usa-at-2023-panamerican-games-in-first-appearance-since-2007 |access-date=August 14, 2025 |website=[[United States Soccer Federation]]}}</ref> The United States conceded a late goal after Freeman was substituted off as they lost their opening match 1–0 against [[Brazil national under-23 football team|Brazil]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=October 24, 2023 |title=USA Falls to Brazil 1-0 on Late Goal After Hard-Fought Effort in First Match at 2023 Pan American Games |url=https://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2023/10/usa-falls-to-brazil-on-late-goal-after-hard-fought-effort-in-first-match-at-2023-pan-american-games |access-date=August 14, 2025 |website=[[United States Soccer Federation]]}}</ref> In the following match against [[Honduras national under-23 football team|Honduras]], Freeman assisted [[Theodore Ku-DiPietro]]'s winning goal to help end the game 2–1.<ref>{{Cite web |date=October 26, 2023 |title=Late Goals from Daniel Leyva and Theodore Ku-DiPietro Boost USA to 2-1 Comeback Win against Honduras at 2023 Pan American Games |url=https://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2023/10/late-goals-from-daniel-leyva-theodore-ku-dipietro-boost-usa-2-1-win-honduras-2023-pan-american-games |access-date=August 14, 2025 |website=[[United States Soccer Federation]]}}</ref> Freeman started again the following match as the United States defeated [[Colombia national under-23 football team|Colombia]] 2–0 in the final group stage match in order to advance to the knockouts.<ref>{{Cite web |date=October 29, 2023 |title=U.S. Men's Pan American Team Secures Spot in Tournament Semifinals with 2-0 Victory against Colombia |url=https://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2023/10/us-mens-pan-american-team-secures-spot-in-tournament-semifinals-with-2-0-victory-against-colombia |access-date=August 14, 2025 |website=[[United States Soccer Federation]]}}</ref> However, the United States were eliminated by hosts, [[Chile Olympic football team|Chile]], after conceding two unanswered goals.<ref>{{Cite web |date=November 1, 2023 |title=U.S. Men's Pan American Team Falls 1-0 to Host Chile in Hard-Fought Semifinal |url=https://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2023/11/us-mens-pan-american-team-falls-1-0-to-host-chile-in-hard-fought-semifinal |access-date=August 14, 2025 |website=[[United States Soccer Federation]]}}</ref>

=== Senior ===
[[File:Alex Freeman 2025 Gold Cup final (cropped).jpg|thumb|right|300x300px|Freeman with the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]] in 2025.]]

On May 22, 2025, Freeman was called up by [[United States men's national soccer team|United States national team]] coach [[Mauricio Pochettino]] for training camp in [[Chicago]] ahead of matches against [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]] and [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=May 22, 2025 |title=Pochettino Names 27-Player Roster for Training Camp ahead of June Matches Against Turkey and Switzerland |url=https://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2025/05/mauricio-pochettino-27-player-roster-training-camp-june-matches-turkey-switzerland |access-date=May 22, 2025 |website=[[United States Soccer Federation]]}}</ref> Freeman later said that receiving the call-up was an "unexpected surprise", but that it was a result of "the hard work I've been putting out the past 3–4 years" and that his father, [[Antonio Freeman]], told him to "keep [his] head down".<ref>{{Cite news |last=Gramajo |first=Mike |date=24 May 2025 |title=Alex Freeman named to US Soccer's pre-Gold Cup training camp |url=https://www.wesh.com/article/orlando-citys-alex-freeman-us-june-training-camp-gold-cup/64868722 |access-date=27 May 2025 |work=[[WESH]]}}</ref> On June 5, Freeman was selected for the [[2025 CONCACAF Gold Cup]],<ref>{{Cite web |date=June 5, 2025 |title=Mauricio Pochettino Selects 26-player Roster for 2025 Concacaf Gold Cup |url=https://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2025/06/usmnt-mauricio-pochettino-selects-26-player-roster-2025-concacaf-gold-cup |access-date=June 5, 2025 |website=[[United States Soccer Federation]]}}</ref> and two days later Freeman started against Turkey as they lost 2–1.<ref>{{Cite news |date=June 7, 2025 |title=Turkey rallies for 2-1 win in friendly against US, which loses 3rd straight under Pochettino |url=https://apnews.com/article/united-states-turkey-score-4100af0d3c46d20b20823f2c5a39e5e9 |access-date=June 7, 2025 |work=[[Associated Press]]}}</ref> Ten days later, Freeman made his competitive debut for the national team when he started and played the full match of the United States' 5–0 win over [[Trinidad and Tobago national football team|Trinidad and Tobago]] in the first match of the group stage.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Goff |first=Steven |date=June 15, 2025 |title=USMNT finds some good energy as it breezes by Trinidad and Tobago |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/sports/2025/06/15/usmnt-trinidad-tobago-gold-cup/ |access-date=June 15, 2025 |work=[[The Washington Post]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Game Details |url=https://www.concacaf.com/en/gold-cup/game-details?competition=f51991ex45qhp1p3iu74u4d4e&season=5r564yyrugptqzsrsphcyk7pw&match=7neii12xn1ai5qtkgg1c4by8k |access-date=June 15, 2025 |website=[[CONCACAF]]}}</ref> The United States advanced to the final of the tournament where they were defeated 2–1 by [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]].<ref name=":2">{{Cite news |last=Deen |first=Safid |last2=Reineking |first2=Jim |date=July 6, 2025 |title=Mexico defeats USMNT to win Concacaf Gold Cup: Highlights from final in Houston |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/soccer/2025/07/06/concacaf-gold-cup-final-2025-usmnt-mexico/84461702007/ |access-date=July 6, 2025 |work=[[USA Today]]}}</ref> Freeman's start against Mexico made him the youngest player to make six consecutive starts for the national team during the tournament.<ref>{{Cite web |date=July 6, 2025 |title=USMNT vs. Mexico: Starting XI & Lineup Notes |url=https://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2025/07/usmnt-mexico-starting-lineup-notes-tyler-adams-diego-luna |access-date=July 7, 2025 |website=[[United States Soccer Federation]]}}</ref>

Freeman received another call-up on August 26 for friendly matches against [[South Korea national football team|South Korea]] and [[Japan national football team|Japan]] on September 6 and 9 respectively.<ref>{{Cite web |date=August 26, 2025 |title=USMNT Head Coach Mauricio Pochettino to Bring 23 Players for September Training Camp ahead of Matches against World Cup Qualified Nations Korea Republic and Japan |url=https://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2025/08/usmnt-head-coach-mauricio-pochettino-23-players-september-training-camp-ahead-of-matches-world-cup-qualified-korea-republic-japan |access-date=August 26, 2025 |website=[[United States Soccer Federation]]}}</ref> Freeman was called up again for friendlies against [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador]] and [[Australia men's national soccer team|Australia]] on October 10 and October 14, respectively, and for the final call-up window for friendlies against [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]] and [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] on November 15 and November 18 respectively.<ref>{{Cite web |date=October 2, 2025 |title=USMNT Head Coach Mauricio Pochettino Selects 26 Players for October Training Camp Ahead of Matches Against World Cup Qualified Nations Ecuador and Australia |url=https://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2025/10/usmnt-head-coach-mauricio-pochettino-selects-26-players-for-october-training-camp-ahead-of-matches-against-world-cup-qualified-nations-ecuador-and-australia |access-date=October 2, 2025 |website=[[United States Soccer Federation]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=November 6, 2025 |title=USMNT Head Coach Mauricio Pochettino Selects 25 Players For November Training Camp Ahead of Matches Against World Cup-Qualified Nations Paraguay and Uruguay |url=https://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2025/11/pochettino-roster-25-players-november-matches-vs-world-cup-bound-paraguay-uruguay |access-date=November 6, 2025 |website=[[United States Soccer Federation]]}}</ref> In the match against Paraguay, which ultimately ended in a 2–1 victory, Freeman attempted to retrieve the ball after it went out of play for a United States throw-in and ended up in a scuffle with Paraguay's [[Gustavo Gómez]] in which Gómez appeared to put Freeman into a headlock. Their altercation resulted in a fight breaking out between the staff and players of the teams and a red card for Paraguay's [[Omar Alderete]] and yellow cards for [[Júnior Alonso]] and Freeman's teammate [[Cristian Roldan]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Cattry |first=Pardeep |date=November 15, 2025 |title=USMNT vs. Paraguay match ends in fight as Alex Freeman, Gustavo Gomez lose their cool in final moments |url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/usmnt-paraguay-fight-alex-freeman-gustavo-gomez-usa-soccer/ |access-date=November 15, 2025 |work=[[CBS News]] |department=[[CBS Sports]] |publisher=[[CBS]]}}</ref> On November 18, Freeman scored a brace against Uruguay, his first senior international goals of his career, and was named Man of the Match.<ref name=":6" /><ref>{{Cite web |last=McAfee |first=Sandy |date=November 19, 2025 |title=Alex Freeman Shines For USMNT In Rout Over Uruguay |url=https://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2025/11/orlando-city-alex-freeman-first-international-goal-brace-usmnt-vs-uruguay |access-date=November 19, 2025 |website=[[United States Soccer Federation]]}}</ref> The United States would ultimately win 5–1.<ref name=":6">{{Cite news |last=Bailey |first=Michael |date=November 18, 2025 |title=USMNT vs Uruguay live updates: Berhalter, Freeman leads US to memorable friendly win |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/live-blogs/usmnt-vs-uruguay-live-updates-score-result/NPIGGA0HXScu/ |access-date=November 18, 2025 |work=[[The New York Times]] |department=[[The Athletic]]}}</ref> Freeman was nominated by the [[United States Soccer Federation]] as a candidate for the [[U.S. Soccer Player of the Year|USMNT Player of the Year]] alongside [[Chris Richards (soccer)|Chris Richards]], [[Maximilian Arfsten]], [[Matt Freese]], and [[Malik Tillman]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.si.com/soccer/usmnt-player-of-the-year-2025-nominees|title=USMNT Player of the Year: Full List of 2025 Nominees|last=Mallow|first=Max|date=December 1, 2025|access-date=December 1, 2025|work=[[Sports Illustrated]]}}</ref>

On March 17, 2026, Freeman received his first call-up of the year for friendly matches at [[Mercedes-Benz Stadium]] in [[Atlanta]] against [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] and [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] on March 28 and 31 respectively.<ref>{{Cite news |date=March 17, 2026 |title=Nine MLS players make USMNT roster for March friendlies |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/nine-mls-players-make-usmnt-roster-march-friendlies--flm-2026-03-17/ |access-date=March 17, 2026 |work=[[Reuters]]}}</ref> On May 26, Freeman's selection for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]] squad was officially revealed, and with his selection he became the first  player to progress from Orlando City's academy and go on to play at the tournament.<ref>{{Cite news |date=May 26, 2026 |title=World Cup 2026: Former Orlando City SC defender Alex Freeman named to USMNT roster |url=https://www.fox35orlando.com/news/former-orlando-city-sc-defender-alex-freeman-named-u-s-world-cup-roster |access-date=May 26, 2026 |work=[[WOFL]]}}</ref>

== Style of play ==
Freeman is both a playmaker and a goal-scoring threat from the fullback position who likes to provide a goal-scoring threat inside the [[penalty area]].<ref name=":3" /> Freeman uses his speed and height to be both an effective attacker as well as an imposing defender.<ref>{{Cite web |last=David |first=Austin |date=June 4, 2025 |title=Forged in Orlando: Alex Freeman on his journey from Orlando City Academy to the U.S. Men's National Team |url=https://www.orlandocitysc.com/news/forged-in-orlando-alex-freeman-on-his-journey-from-orlando-city-academy-to-the-u-s-men-s-national-team |access-date=July 14, 2025 |website=[[Orlando City SC|Orlando City]]}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Freeman is the son of former professional [[American football|football]] player [[Antonio Freeman]], who played as a [[wide receiver]] and won [[Super Bowl XXXI]] with the [[Green Bay Packers]] in 1997.<ref>{{cite web |last=Gramajo |first=Mike |title=Orlando City locks up Alex Freeman with 4-year deal |url=https://www.orlandosentinel.com/sports/os-sp-orlando-city-signing-0216-20220215-aryyj5lb6zabnn4lycc54pwofu-story.html |website=orlandosentinel.com |date=February 15, 2022 |access-date=March 26, 2022 |archive-date=March 12, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220312145412/https://www.orlandosentinel.com/sports/os-sp-orlando-city-signing-0216-20220215-aryyj5lb6zabnn4lycc54pwofu-story.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=":1" /> In his youth, Freeman played both [[basketball]] and soccer alongside his father's sport and described having a "secret love for soccer". Freeman was initially hesitant to tell his father that he wasn't interested in pursuing American football, but that choosing soccer was a "clear choice" for him.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Hernandez |first=Cesar |date=June 17, 2025 |title=USMNT's Freeman says 'secret love for soccer' guided youth choice |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/45532026/usa-alex-freeman-secret-love-soccer |access-date=October 23, 2025 |work=[[ESPN]]}}</ref>

Freeman's mother, Rochelle, is a [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] fan and jokingly calls Freeman her "little [[Trent Alexander-Arnold]]".<ref name=":1" /> Freeman also has two younger brothers, Tyler and Josh, who both play soccer as well.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Litman |first=Laken |date=June 28, 2025 |title=Who is Alex Freeman? U.S. defender on the World Cup, his dad and fútbol over football |url=https://www.foxsports.com/stories/soccer/who-is-usmnt-defender-alex-freeman-gold-cup |access-date=November 6, 2025 |work=[[Fox Sports]]}}</ref>

